data.title: Andrew Bynum, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Andrew Bynum stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Andrew Bynum - Points

Andrew Bynum scores a career high 42 points (2009)

On January 21, 2009, Andrew Bynum set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 42 points in LA Lakers's road win against LA Clippers, 97-108. He also had 15 rebounds and 3 blocks. He shot 17/24 from two, shooting at 70.8% from the field. He also shot 8/11 from the free-throw line.

Andrew Bynum - Rebounds

Andrew Bynum grabs a career high 30 rebounds (2012)

On April 11, 2012, Andrew Bynum set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 30 rebounds in LA Lakers's road win against San Antonio, 84-98. He also had 16 points, 2 assists and 2 blocks.

Andrew Bynum - Assists

Andrew Bynum gives a career high 6 assists (2011)

On February 03, 2011, Andrew Bynum set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 6 assists in LA Lakers's home loss against San Antonio, 88-89. He also had 10 points, 10 rebounds and 3 blocks.

Andrew Bynum - Steals

Andrew Bynum has a career high 3 steals (2007)

On October 30, 2007, Andrew Bynum tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 3 steals in LA Lakers's home loss against Houston, 93-95. He also had 4 points, 4 rebounds and 2 assists.

Andrew Bynum - Blocks

Andrew Bynum blocks a career high 7 shots (2007)

On January 26, 2007, Andrew Bynum tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 7 blocks in LA Lakers's home loss against Charlotte, 97-106. He also had 11 points, 16 rebounds and 1 assist.
